[{"location":"VersionChanges/","page":"Version Change Log","title":"Version Change Log","text":"info: v0.0.1\nChangesCreated base version of the package","category":"page"},{"location":"#LinearHypothesisTest","page":"Home","title":"LinearHypothesisTest","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"GitHub Repo: https://github.com/eohne/LinearHypothesisTest.jl","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Perform Linear Hypothesis Tests. Currently allows to test hypothesis of the following form for GLM and FixedEffectModels models:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":" beta_1 = beta_2\n beta_2 + 3 times beta_2 =5\n 05 times beta_1 + beta_2 + beta_3 = beta_4\n 05 times beta_1 + beta_2 + beta_3 = 0","category":"page"},{"location":"#Package-Installation","page":"Home","title":"Package Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The package is NOT registered with the General Registry but you can install the package either by using the Pkg REPL mode (press ] to enter):","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"pkg> add http://github.com/eohne/LinearHypothesisTest.jl","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"or by using Pkg functions","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> using Pkg; Pkg.add(\"http://github.com/eohne/LinearHypothesisTest.jl\")","category":"page"},{"location":"#Function-Definition","page":"Home","title":"Function Definition","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"LinearHypothesisTests","category":"page"},{"location":"#LinearHypothesisTest.LinearHypothesisTests","page":"Home","title":"LinearHypothesisTest.LinearHypothesisTests","text":"LinearHypothesisTests\n\n#Fields\n\ntest::String The type of test.\nse::Number Standard error\nval::Number Value of the test statistic (F or Chis val)\npvalue::Number The pvalue\ncrit::Number The critical value for the 5% sign. level\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Example","page":"Home","title":"Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The below regression etc are just toy examples to show how the functions work.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Load-some-required-packages-and-data:","page":"Home","title":"Load some required packages and data:","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using GLM, FixedEffectModels, CSV, DataFrames\nusing LinearHypothesisTest\ndata = CSV.File(\"test/lalonde.csv\") |> DataFrame;\n\nm_lm =  lm(@formula(treat ~ age + educ + race + married + nodegree ),data);\nm_glm =  glm(@formula(treat ~ age + educ + race + married + nodegree ),data,Binomial(),LogitLink());\nm_fe = reg(data,@formula(treat ~ age + educ + race + married + nodegree  + fe(re74)),Vcov.cluster(:Column1));","category":"page"},{"location":"#Example-Linear-Model-(GLM)-m_lm","page":"Home","title":"Example Linear Model (GLM) m_lm","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> m_lm\nStatsModels.TableRegressionModel{LinearModel{GLM.LmResp{Vector{Float64}}, GLM.DensePredChol{Float64, LinearAlgebra.CholeskyPivoted{Float64, Matrix{Float64}, Vector{Int64}}}}, Matrix{Float64}}\n\ntreat ~ 1 + age + educ + race + married + nodegree\n\nCoefficients:\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n                    Coef.  Std. Error       t  Pr(>|t|)    Lower 95%    Upper 95%\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n(Intercept)    0.371995    0.126153      2.95    0.0033   0.124247     0.619744\nage            0.00135367  0.00164096    0.82    0.4097  -0.00186898   0.00457632\neduc           0.0183177   0.00818698    2.24    0.0256   0.00223943   0.0343959\nrace: hispan  -0.449351    0.0497604    -9.03    <1e-17  -0.547075    -0.351628\nrace: white   -0.539054    0.0334271   -16.13    <1e-48  -0.604701    -0.473407\nmarried       -0.109849    0.0336998    -3.26    0.0012  -0.176031    -0.0436663\nnodegree       0.103103    0.0439286     2.35    0.0192   0.0168322    0.189373\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Let's test if the coefficent of age + 2*educ = married:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> LinearHypothesisTests(m_lm, \"age + 2*educ = married\")\n\nF-Test\n------------------------------\nSt Error:               0.037\nValue:                  15.9\n5% Crit Value:          3.857\nP-Value:                0.01%\n------------------------------","category":"page"},{"location":"#Example-Logit-Model-(GLM)-m_glm","page":"Home","title":"Example Logit Model (GLM) m_glm","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> m_glm\nStatsModels.TableRegressionModel{GeneralizedLinearModel{GLM.GlmResp{Vector{Float64}, Binomial{Float64}, LogitLink}, GLM.DensePredChol{Float64, LinearAlgebra.CholeskyPivoted{Float64, Matrix{Float64}, Vector{Int64}}}}, Matrix{Float64}}\n\ntreat ~ 1 + age + educ + race + married + nodegree\n\nCoefficients:\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n                   Coef.  Std. Error       z  Pr(>|z|)   Lower 95%   Upper 95%\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n(Intercept)   -1.55217     0.975408    -1.59    0.1115  -3.46394     0.35959\nage            0.0102973   0.0132934    0.77    0.4386  -0.0157572   0.0363518\neduc           0.151612    0.0656824    2.31    0.0210   0.0228773   0.280348\nrace: hispan  -2.12709     0.363592    -5.85    <1e-08  -2.83972    -1.41446\nrace: white   -3.12657     0.285138   -10.97    <1e-27  -3.68543    -2.5677\nmarried       -0.929693    0.271283    -3.43    0.0006  -1.4614     -0.397989\nnodegree       0.787192    0.335072     2.35    0.0188   0.130463    1.44392\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Let's test whether age + educ =0","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> LinearHypothesisTests(m_glm, \"age + educ = 0\")\n\nF-Test\n------------------------------\nSt Error:               0.069\nValue:                  5.429\n5% Crit Value:          3.857\nP-Value:                2.01%\n------------------------------","category":"page"},{"location":"#Fixed-Effects-Example:","page":"Home","title":"Fixed Effects Example:","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> m_fe\n                                 FixedEffectModel\n==================================================================================\nNumber of obs:                       266  Converged:                          true\ndof (model):                           6  dof (residuals):                     265\nR²:                                0.359  R² adjusted:                       0.320\nF-statistic:                     19.0944  P-value:                           0.000\nR² within:                         0.294  Iterations:                            1\n==================================================================================\n                 Estimate  Std. Error    t-stat  Pr(>|t|)    Lower 95%   Upper 95%\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nage            0.00445118  0.00324399   1.37213    0.1712  -0.00193609   0.0108385\neduc           0.0220794   0.0137164    1.60971    0.1087  -0.00492753   0.0490864\nrace: hispan  -0.423725    0.100488    -4.21668    <1e-04  -0.621581    -0.225869\nrace: white   -0.531621    0.0599516   -8.86749    <1e-15  -0.649663    -0.413578\nmarried       -0.130539    0.0730434   -1.78715    0.0751  -0.274359     0.0132798\nnodegree       0.0991155   0.0807286    1.22776    0.2206  -0.0598355    0.258066\n==================================================================================","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> LinearHypothesisTests(m_fe, \"age + educ + race: hispan = married\")\n\nF-Test\n------------------------------\nSt Error:               0.14\nValue:                  3.611\n5% Crit Value:          3.877\nP-Value:                5.85%\n------------------------------","category":"page"}]
